cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.MA, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the integration of ambient backscatter with wireless powered communication networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a novel hybrid transmitter design and introduces a multiple access scheme, which involves information theory concepts such as channel coding and modulation. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the cognitive radio environment and the coordination of hybrid data transmissions, which involves security and privacy concerns. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper proposes a multiple access scheme to coordinate the hybrid data transmissions, which involves the interaction of multiple agents. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the performance evaluation of the hybrid transmitter design, which involves system modeling and control.
